<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1484,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">
This species was described based on a single male from 
<collectingCountry box="[824,945,1557,1583]" name="Guatemala" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[959,1109,1557,1583]" country="Guatemala" name="Alta Verapaz" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Alta Verapaz</collectingRegion>
), deposited at 
<collectionCode box="[1267,1347,1557,1583]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">SMFD</collectionCode>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A. &amp; Hovore, F. T." pageId="1" pageNumber="554" refId="ref6271" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Hovore, F. T. (2006) Checklist of the Cerambycidae, or longhorned wood-boring beetles, of the Western Hemisphere. Bio Quip Publications, Rancho Dominguez, 394 pp." type="book" year="2006">Monné &amp; Hovore (2006)</bibRefCitation>
reported it from 
<collectingCountry box="[547,660,1593,1619]" name="Honduras" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Honduras</collectingCountry>
. The following variations were observed in the specimen examined: base of the elytra reddish (black in the 
<typeStatus box="[582,685,1629,1656]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">holotype</typeStatus>
); pronotum slightly lighter (black in the 
<typeStatus box="[1135,1238,1629,1656]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">holotype</typeStatus>
); antennomere IV about as long as scape (respectively with 
<quantity box="[620,721,1665,1691]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.12" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" unit="mm" value="1.12">1.12 mm</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[777,877,1664,1691]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.50 mm</quantity>
in the 
<typeStatus box="[956,1059,1665,1692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">holotype</typeStatus>
); yellowish bands on elytra fused along suture (not fused in the 
<typeStatus box="[508,611,1701,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">holotype</typeStatus>
); profemora yellowish brown except extreme brownish apex (peduncle yellowish brown and club dark brown in the holotype—the club was described as being reddish brown, but the photograph of the 
<typeStatus box="[356,454,1773,1799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">holotype</typeStatus>
shows it is dark brown); meso- and metafemora mostly yellowish brown, with irregular brownish macula on center of the sides of the posterior half (peduncle yellowish brown, dark brown on club—the club was described as being reddish brown, but the photograph of the 
<typeStatus box="[958,1056,1845,1871]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">holotype</typeStatus>
shows it is dark brown in on the meso- and metafemora).
</paragraph>
